narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It basically functions as a lecture about various aspects of ancient Egyptian medicine.
don't take it unless you know a ton about the subject already.

This class probably shouldn't be cross listed as HSHM- it's really reliant on knowing some Egyptian, or at the very least caring about how semantics come into play- I hoped for a more in depth analysis of egyptian medical practice based on anatomy, rather than one based on linguistics. Nonetheless, I liked the class.
Intriguing material, very good professor. While the class can be a bit dry at times, take the course if you have any interest in the subject.
